You can now send a Speech Message, which will be read out to the recipient. This was a user request. (WinXP Only)
Pressing F1 anywhere in Network Chat will display help relative to that window.
You can use a Custom Name by setting it in the Chat/Options menu.
If you have 'Minimise to System Tray' turned on, and 'Popup Window on Incoming Message' turned off, you will see a nice yellow bubble containing the incoming message. (Win2k/XP Only)
Network Chat now lets you set your font and size. This was a user request.
You can include Emoticons in your display name! Try it!
You can send a message to another network chat user over the internet by entering their IP address in the Network Config window
